I"<p><b>Problem</b><br />
If $n \in N,$ then $1 + (-1)^n(2n-1)$ is a multiple of $4$.
<br /></p>
<hr />

<p><br />
<b>Proof.</b><br />
Suppose $n \in N$.</p>
<div center="">
$$
\begin{align*}
gcd(a,b) = gcd(a,b-a) = gcd(a,b+a)
\end{align*}
$$
</div>
<p>Proof: Let \(gcd(a,b) = d \in Z\). By the defintion of \(gcd\) we know that \(d \ | \ a\) and \(d \ | \ b\). Therefore, for some \(x, y \in Z\), we have \(a = xd\) and, \(b = yd\). From this we have, \(a - b = d(x - y)\). Therefore, we know that \(d = gcd(a,b) \ | \ a - b\).</p>

